PN,44305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1773508276
OL,3,CPM meets with the Taoiseach in Co Cork
OL,4,Cfor the second UK-Ireland Summit
OL,6,FThe Government of Ireland is also
OL,7,Frepresented by Tanaiste and Finance
OL,8,FMinister Simon Harris, Foreign
OL,9,FAffairs, Trade and Defence Minister
OL,10,FHelen McEntee, Energy and Transport
OL,11,FMinister Darragh O'Brien, and Justice
OL,12,FMinister Jim O'Callaghan.
OL,14,FThe first UK-Ireland Summit took place
OL,15,Fin Liverpool in March last year, as
OL,16,Fpart of what the Taoiseach and Prime
OL,17,FMinister hailed as a "reset" in
OL,18,Frelations which brought about enhanced
OL,19,Fco-operation on projects to 2030.
OL,26,@yD@VOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/7
